# Git commit

## Gate

**Never `git commit` without explicit user confirmation.**

## Message format

### Subject (line 1)

- **Imperative**, concise, ≤ ~72 chars when possible.
- Optional scope: `[VulkanDesktop]`, `[Cursor]`, `[Docs]`, `[Lighting]`, `[Gfx]`.

Good:

```
Fix OBJ mesh load crash when UV coordinates are missing.
[VulkanDesktop] Add FPS fly camera with input snapshot and ImGui tuning
Move completed P0 line to Docs/Archived-Plan.md (task-only).
```

Avoid: `fixed stuff`, `WIP`, `Update files`.

### Body (optional)

Blank line after subject; 1–3 sentences on motivation / verification.

## Docs task close (in commit body if relevant)

- Move completed line Active-Plan → Archived-Plan (`[P0]`…`[P4]` or legacy `[Sx]`).
- Update `EngineArchitecture.md` **only** on locked policy change (`docs-roadmap-arch-sync.mdc`).
- Prefer one logical change per commit; split implementation vs policy when both land.
